McKenzie and Matthew’s wedding this past weekend was nothing short of a dream. Their tented wedding on the land McKenzie grew up on right next to the water was so meaningful to her. It was glamorous, beautiful, everything pink and so much fun. You have to see McKenzie’s stunning custom dress by @nardosdesign and I wish I could relive their first look over and over again. It was the sweetest thing I’ve ever seen. I love how Matthew was just taken away by her in her dress. Matthew was so happy all day. Something that stood out to me was how McKenzie would tell me about each of her bridesmaids and friends and how long they were in her life. I know she loved having them be a part of her wedding day and having them be by her side. Every single person there to support them on their wedding day was so loved and meaningful to them. That’s what it’s all about! Congratulations McKenzie and Matthew!! Adore you.

Today someone asked me what the most unique or favorite wedding I’ve ever photographed. I always say I don’t really have a favorite (because I just don’t…I love sooo many of our couples and so many elements of each wedding) but I tried to name some weddings that were unique. I started by saying ‘well, I photographed a wedding at a palace in Portugal once, beautiful wedding in the vineyards in Virginia…oh recently a couple had a wedding in their family land and did a tent and everything was pink and there were gorgeous rentals and florals on the ceiling and under a clear dance floor….oh oh wait and the couple this last weekend they were soooooo sweet and so immersed in the weekend and just having the best time ever and I loved it so much.’ Then I stopped and told her…‘they’re all so unique, every wedding is unique and that’s why photographing them is so fun.’ She said ‘you really like what you do huh?’ And yes, yes I do. 

Yesterday, I had quite the adventure with the most fun couple at their engagement session and the groom asked me how long I’ve been doing this. I told him 9 years and he asked me if I still like this. If you can’t tell, the answer is of course…yes. Maybe too much? For those that have shot with me you know it’s so fun and I love making art and memories from this. 

I think 10-year-old Erin would be so happy she gets to do what she does as her career. I’m so thankful. 

These images are from a very special day for Kaelan and Patrick who of course, had a very unique and wonderful wedding day. They were married at Kaelan’s family home and had a beautiful garden wedding. I absolutely loved the little outdoor chapel they created for their ceremony. The reception was straight out of a fairytale. I could relive this day over and over again! I just adore these two! Planning and design @aislebewithyouweddings florals @anthousai

Well hello, it’s me, Erin. I’m getting used to showing my face on instagram more and more. I mentioned in a post the other day that I’ve been photographing weddings for nine years. That also means I’ve been posting here for that long (and longer) and I still never get used to showing up personally but I try. My friend Kati took some beautiful photos of me and my family the other day so I have a little to share. 

So a little about me, I actually really love art and painting and long story short that is what lead me to photography. I also love interior design, renovating homes and everything that comes with that. I love a good dinner party and cooking for others. I have recently been into gardening and I’m trying my hand at that…we’ll see how it goes. I have texture issues and I cannot touch wooden spoons. I cannot explain it. I love my two children, my daughter Penelope and my son Emerson more than the world itself and everything I do I do for them. 

For those that know what it’s like to be in front of my camera you know that I absolutely love being a photographer. I can get into a shoot and tell you how absolutely perfect and beautiful you are (because I just adore people). I’m so very thankful I get to make art with a camera as my job.

Oh hey, it’s me, Erin. Just me and my little travel film camera. 

I recently had dinner with some photographer friends of mine. I met them because they took a workshop I taught years ago and then through the past years I guess I’ve somewhat mentored them and then become friends. What’s funny is, the student became the encourager to me because months ago…maybe even a year ago they got on to me. They said ‘ummm, you really need to share more of yourself online!’ They had all kinds of reasons to back that up but I won’t go into detail. I will share that I’m a little shy online. Who can share in those feelings?! I know many people can. It’s difficult to want to be seen. That’s why hiding behind the camera is so easy in this job and hiding behind my work is sooo much easier. However, after many months of thinking about my fellow photographers encouragement and the student teaching the teacher if you will. I am here. It is me, hi! I’ve been dipping my toes in the water here and there and trying to show up online a little more in the past months but I think I’m going to take it a bit further. Ya ready?! I have a few fun surprises. 

Oh, and thank you for the encouragement @cameronandelizabeth love ya!! And you’re killing it.

I’ve been a little inspired by the ocean recently (thanks to a trip to the beach) and pearls and petals and waves have been really popping out to me a ton. I was scrolling through some images I took and this one stopped me. I love how we create art from nature when when we don’t know it. This dress reminds me of all of those things and something different all in the same thing. Even just the way you photograph something can tell a certain story that you want to tell. Did you know that it is my love for art, as in drawing and painting, that drew me to photography. I’ve been taking art classes since 7th or 8th grade and it’s the creating a little piece of art that I love so much. It can be just a pretty piece of art, a thoughtful piece of art, one that holds memories, one that just means something to me, one that means something to another, so on and so on. That’s how I got here and that’s why I love it so. I just had to figure out how to do something I love so much every single day. 

So this is me, Erin, the artist behind the camera. The other day I was complimenting a mother-of-the bride on her outfit (she was quite stylish) and she said “oh that means so much coming from you, you’re an artist.” It was such an impactful comment to me and she didn’t event know it. Sometimes we can get lost behind the camera taking thousands of photos and memories and it can feel routine. Her comment snapped me back and helped remember why I do this to begin with. Such perfect timing too because I’ve been in the middle of planning some fun rebranding and some shoots. It’s been so long since I’ve done anything like that and I needed to remember why I love it. 

I can’t wait to paint with my camera. Every day. 

Image taken by my dear friend and most precious mother @katimallory

This moment where Mallory’s mom and mother-in-law were helping her getting ready in her wedding day was so so sweet. I knew I was going to love this first image and I really knew they were going to love this set of images. Holds such a sweet memory! Here are just a few sweet photos from their wedding day.

I hope you’re having a wonderful new year. At the start of every new year I reflect back on the past year. 2023 brought me to a ton of places I never thought I’d go (physically, mentally and metaphorically) and I’m so grateful for it all. I was quite literally coast to coast several times photographing such wonderful sessions and weddings. I moved from Arkansas to Dallas and so much more in between. It doesn’t matter that I’ve been doing this 9+ years I’m still just so excited every year and every trip and every couple that I meet. 

This year I noticed that every wedding I was photographing I was even more immersed in the day and with each family and couple that at the end of the wedding I would feel like ‘oh wait it’s over?!’ I feel like that says something good. So for that, I know that 2024 is going to be even more wonderful and I am excited for all that it holds. I still can’t believe I get to make art for a living and work with such incredible couples. Don’t wake me if I’m dreaming. 

So grateful for all that follow along, couples that choose me to document their beautiful weddings and to make beautiful art. Happy New Year to you all.
